### Test Authentication Endpoints

### 1. Signup Attendee
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "attendee",
  "termsAccepted": true
}

### 2. Signup Organizer
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Jane Smith",
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "organizer",
  "termsAccepted": true,
  "organizationName": "Event Co",
  "organizationWebsite": "https://eventco.com",
  "contactNumber": "+251911123456"
}

### 3. Login
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Verify Email (replace TOKEN with actual token from email)
GET http://localhost:3001/auth/verify-email?token=TOKEN

### 5. Forgot Password
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

### 6. Reset Password (replace TOKEN with actual token from email)
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "TOKEN",
  "newPassword": "newpassword123"
}

### 7. Get Profile (replace JWT_TOKEN with actual token from login)
GET http://localhost:3001/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer JWT_TOKEN

### 8. Admin Only Endpoint (replace JWT_TOKEN with admin token)
GET http://localhost:3001/auth/admin-only
Authorization: Bearer JWT_TOKEN

### 9. Organizer/Admin Endpoint (replace JWT_TOKEN with organizer/admin token)
GET http://localhost:3001/auth/organizer-admin
Authorization: Bearer JWT_TOKEN

### 10. Google OAuth (open in browser)
GET http://localhost:3001/auth/google